ModulePrefs.title: Dynamic Iframe Gadget
ModulePrefs.description: Using iframe to include URL to your site which support dynamic height.

UserPref.name: dynamic
UserPref.display_name: Auto size the frame height by content

Module.Content:
<style>
		.loading-use-flexbox{
			display:flex;
			align-items:center;
			justify-content:center;
			width:100%;
			height:200px;
		}

		.loadingImg{
			height:200px;
			width:200px;
			background-repeat: no-repeat;
			background-image:url('data:image/gif;base64,');
		}
	</style>
	<div id="loading" class="loading-use-flexbox">
		<div class="loadingImg"></div>
	</div>
	
    <div id='iframeDiv'></div>
	
	<script type="text/javascript">
  
		gadgets.util.registerOnLoadHandler(onload);
		
		var dynamic = "";
		
		function onload(){
		//variables
		var prefs = new gadgets.Prefs();
		var url = prefs.getString('url');
		var scroll = prefs.getString('scroll');
		dynamic = prefs.getString('dynamic');
		var height = 300;
		var width = 300;
		
		if(gadgets.window){
			var viewport = gadgets.window.getViewportDimensions();
			if(viewport.width){
				var width = viewport.width;
			}
			if(viewport.height){
				var height = viewport.height;
			}
		}
		
		var iframe = document.createElement('iframe');
		iframe.setAttribute('width',width+'px');
		iframe.setAttribute('height',height+'px');
		
		iframe.setAttribute('frameborder','no');
		iframe.setAttribute('onload','loaded(this)');
		
		if(scroll){
			iframe.setAttribute('scrolling',scroll);
		}
		iframe.setAttribute('src', url);
		
		var iframeDiv = document.getElementById('iframeDiv');
		iframeDiv.appendChild(iframe);    
	}
  
	function loaded(frame){
		document.getElementById('loading').style.display = "none";
		if(dynamic == "yes"){
			try{
				var height = frame.contentWindow.document.body.scrollHeight + 'px';
				frame.style.height = height;
				gadgets.window.adjustHeight(height);
				gadgets.window.adjustHeight();
				console.log(frame.src);
			}catch(error){}
		}
	}
</script>
